The paper focuses on using deep learning techniques for medical image analysis, specifically for detecting lesions in radiology images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses unsupervised and supervised learning methods, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of clinical annotations and the creation of a large-scale dataset also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for natural language processing (cs.CL) to improve the accuracy of lesion detection.
